         </div>
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <div class="msup">
          <div class="mrow">
           <span class="mi">l</span>
          </div>
          <span class="mn">2</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <span stretchy="true" class="mo">)</span>
       </div>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <div accent="true" class="mover">
          <span class="mi">q</span>
          <span class="mo">¯</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">x</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <span class="mn">2</span>
       <span class="mi">k</span>
       <span class="mi">l</span>
       <div class="msub">
        <div class="mrow">
         <div accent="true" class="mover">
          <span class="mi">q</span>
          <span class="mo">¯</span>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">y</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="msup">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span class="mi">K</span>
        </div>
        <span class="mn">4</span>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">.</span>
    </div>
    <div xlink:href="41598_2019_47150_Article_Equ3.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   </div>
  </div>
 </p>
 <p id="Par25" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">To calculate the group velocities, the cubic polynomial of 
  <span class="italic">l</span>, which is derived from equation (
  <a rid="Equ1" ref-type="" href="#Equ1">1</a>), should be solved. Afterwards, the ray path of the Rossby wave activity is determined by the following form: 
  <div id="IEq9" class="inline-formula">
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M23" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\frac{dx}{dt}={c}_{gx}$$\end{document}</span>
    <div id="M24" class="math">
     <div class="mfrac">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">d</span>
       <span class="mi">x</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">d</span>
       <span class="mi">t</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">=</span>
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">c</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <span class="mi">g</span>
       <span class="mi">x</span>
      </div>
